    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L high-compression inline-six engine. This naturally aspirated powerplant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure dual-VANOS system to deliver exceptional throttle response and a linear power band peaking at 8,000 RPM. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis remains structurally sound with documented rear subframe reinforcement, mitigating a known platform weakness. Suspension geometry is maintained via McPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, providing the precise kinematically-tuned handling characteristics expected of the M-division. While the exterior shows minor road wear, the mechanical vitals are robust, the cooling system has been overhauled, and the rod bearings have been serviced, ensuring this E46 is ready for spirited longitudinal and lateral acceleration.",
